HEADWORD: Relativistic
<hw>Rel`a*tiv*ist"ic</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>of, pertaining to, or in conformity with the <er>theory of
relativity</er>; <as>as, the <ex>relativistic</ex> increase of mass with
velocity</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>moving at a speed sufficiently high that the changes
of mass or time dilation predicted by the theory of relativity may be
observed; moving at a significant fraction of the speed of light;
<as>as, <ex>relativistic</ex> electrons</as>.</def>br/
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Relativistic mass equation</ent>⟦br⟧
